    <div id="col1" class="collapse tf-panel-collapse-body">
        <p>FID community licences in the FID Criminology are aimed at professors and academic staff at criminological departments and institutes. They provide free access to selected electronic literature. Users need a KrimDok account in which they preferably provide an institutional email address and indicate the country in which the insitute is located. After searching for the desired licensed title in KrimDok, the link ‘FID-Lizenz: Zugriff mit KrimDok-Konto’ leads to the full text.</p>
        <p>The following licences are currently available:</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 20px;">1) Strafrecht und Kriminologie: Untersuchungen und Forschungsberichte aus dem Max-Planck-Institut für Ausländisches und Internationales Strafrecht, Freiburg im Breisgau.</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 20px;">All 20 volumes of this series are freely accessible and can also be searched using the command *kfl:duncker.</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 20px;">2) Nomos package “Kriminologie” </p>
        <p style="padding-left: 20px;">The FID, together with Nomos Publishing, has put together an e-book package containing a total of 94 criminologically relevant titles. These can also be accessed using the search command *kfl:nomos. Currently, up to 500 users per licence are provided (as of December 2025).</p>
    </div>
</div>

